# New Task Kickoff Trigger

## Core Principles

Design Phase = Human-driven (AI prepares context, human decides direction)
Implementation Phase = AI-driven (After approach confirmation, AI autonomously utilizes Skills chain for efficient execution)

## Trigger Conditions

Trigger the complete kickoff process when any of the following signals are detected in the conversation:

- User mentions: new task / new feature / new design / new module / start working on / tackle / initiate / continue with
- User describes functionality or requirements not yet present in the project
- User references a todo item from Notion / docs / task list
- User says "continue previous work" or similar expressions to restore context

**Do NOT trigger for**: Pure code bug fixes (use `systematic-debugging`), simple configuration adjustments, single-file edits, or Q&A consultations.

## Red Flag Thinking (Quick Check)

| Dangerous Thought | Reality |
|-------------------|---------|
| "This is simple, no need to gather context" | Unchecked assumptions waste the most time |
| "I'll look at the code first" | Gather context first, then look at the code |
| "The user explained it clearly, just do it" | The user's context is in their head, not yours |
| "I did something similar last time, I remember" | You don't remember, go search past conversations |
| "It's just a single file change" | Confirm dependencies before taking action |
| "Start coding, figure it out as I go" | Complete Phase 1-3 first, then act |

## Post-Trigger Actions

Upon detecting the signals above, **immediately use the Read tool to load the complete kickoff protocol**:

Load `new-task-kickoff.mdc` in the following priority order, then strictly execute the Phase 1-4 process within it:

```text
Priority 1: Local global path
  Read ~/.cursor/rules/new-task-kickoff.mdc (AI expands ~ to actual user directory)

Priority 2: Environment initialization and recovery (when local does not exist)
  Execute environment setup script:
    if [ ! -d ~/.cursor/skills ]; then git clone https://github.com/Rokid/agentic-coding-workflow.git ~/.cursor/skills; else cd ~/.cursor/skills && git pull origin main --ff-only 2>/dev/null; fi
    mkdir -p ~/.cursor/rules
    cp ~/.cursor/skills/rules/new-task-kickoff.mdc ~/.cursor/rules/
  Dependency and plugin check:
    - AI automatically checks if necessary Cursor Plugins / MCP Servers are missing
    - If they can be auto-installed via CLI/scripts, do so; otherwise, list them and prompt the user to install manually
  Then re-read the Priority 1 path

Priority 3: Fallback process (when Git recovery also fails)
  1. Search past conversations and related documents
  2. Present context summary
  3. Wait for user to confirm direction
  4. Proceed according to confirmed approach
```

> **Path Strategy**: Both the trigger and the kickoff protocol are global rules, independent of specific project directories. They can be reused in any project.
> Git Repository: `https://github.com/Rokid/agentic-coding-workflow.git` → `rules/new-task-kickoff.mdc`